canonical:
  title: 題畫蟬
  author: 李承召
  language: lzh
  text: 香燒古篆坐蕭然讀盡黃庭內外篇一味天眞無與語畫中相對飮風仙
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 題畫蟬
  author: 李承召
  language: lzh
  text: 香燒古篆坐蕭然。讀盡黃庭內外篇。一味天眞無與語。畫中相對飮風仙。
korean:
  title: 제화선
  author: 이승소
  language: kor
  text: |-
    향을 고전에 사르고 쓸쓸히 앉아
    황정의 내외편을 모두 읽었다
    천진의 한 맛과 더불어 말할 이 없어
    그림 속에서 서로 대하매 바람을 마시는 신선일세
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1450_020_0160&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Inscribed on a Painting of a Cicada
  author: Lee Seung-so
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Incense burns in the pattern of ancient script, and I sit in solitude.
    I have read through all the inner and outer chapters of the Yellow Court.
    With this single taste of celestial truth, there is no one to speak with—
    Yet in the painting, facing each other, we are immortals sipping the wind.
  footnotes:
    - The Yellow Court Classics (黃庭) are Daoist texts associated with inner alchemy and spiritual cultivation
    - The cicada in Chinese and Korean poetry traditionally symbolizes spiritual transcendence and freedom from earthly attachments
